If you're unfamiliar, this is the rare Toybiz 2nd print of Spider-Man 2099 issue 1. It features a plain white border instead of the red foil border on the first print. It also features a barcode, where the 1st print says 2099 in a black corner box or a newstand barcode in some cases. The original came out in 1992, but the 2nd print didn't come out until 9 years later in 2001. It was packaged with a Toybiz action figure of Spider-Man 2099, and because it was packaged with a toy, many didn't make it out of the packaging in a decent condition. You don't see these that often compared to the 1st print, which can be found in any comic shop. If you can manage to get a 9.8 in this particular book, it goes for a pretty good chunk of cash.
